## Shopping Blue Nile Halo Settings for Pear Diamonds: By Review Count

Review count is the most actionable quality signal available when buying an engagement ring setting online. A setting with 91 buyer reviews that shipped, was received, was worn, and was not returned represents a fundamentally different level of confidence than a setting with 1 review or no reviews. In the pear halo category, review counts vary dramatically.

**The 91-review tier — Pavé Diamond Halo Pear by James Allen ($1,555)** is the clear market leader. 91 confirmed buyers across all three metal variants (same count in yellow, white, and rose gold) tells you the setting fits pear centers correctly, the halo follows the pear silhouette as advertised, and The Halo Continuity Rule is respected at the tip. This is the entry-level pear halo setting with the most quality verification behind it. The $1,555 price point, combined with 91 reviews, makes it the default recommendation for first-time pear halo buyers.

**The 39–41 review tier — Classic Halo ($2,300, 39 reviews) and Blue Nile Studio Heiress Halo ($3,585, 41 reviews)** are both strongly buyer-confirmed settings that work with pear centers. The Classic Halo uses a round halo outline (not a pear-specific silhouette) — the round frame around a pear center creates a distinctive "diamond in a circle" look that some buyers prefer for its geometric contrast. The Heiress Halo is a Blue Nile-designed setting with heirloom detailing; its 41 reviews confirm it accepts and displays pear centers correctly.

**The 210-review tier — Round Split Band Halo by James Allen ($4,400–$4,510)** has the highest absolute review count of any setting in this category, though it is not pear-specific. 210 confirmed buyers have received and kept this setting. The split band adds additional accent diamond coverage down the shank from the halo head, creating maximum sparkle from every angle. At $4,400–$4,510, this is a significant investment in the setting alone — but the 210-review assurance at this price point is meaningful.

**The 1-review tier (new pear-specific settings)** — the Pear Shape Side Stone Halo ($3,570–$4,005, 1 review each) and the Ballerina Halo ($3,275, 1 review) are new or low-review configurations where limited buyer data exists. These are purchased based on design appeal rather than confirmed performance. Blue Nile's return policy provides a backstop, but first-buyer risk is higher in this tier.

