## Halo Style Variations: Pavé, French-Cut, Milgrain, Ballerina

Not all halos look alike. The accent diamonds in a halo can be set using different prong styles, bead configurations, and architectural treatments that create meaningfully different aesthetics.

**Pavé halo** is the standard. Small accent diamonds are set with tiny metal beads between them, creating a continuous surface of sparkle. The metal is minimized, the stones are maximized. The Pavé Diamond Halo Pear by James Allen ($1,555) is a pure pavé halo. This is the correct choice for buyers who want maximum brightness and minimum visible metal.

**French-cut pavé** (also called "French cut" or "U-cut" pavé) places the accent diamonds in U-shaped recesses cut into the setting, with the stones seated lower and the prongs more visible between them. French pavé has a vintage, engraved look compared to standard pavé. The Glamour Halo Vintage-Style ($2,770) and the Interlaced Pavé Halo ($1,750) both incorporate French-cut and interlaced pavé details that give them their vintage character. French-cut halos suit buyers who want their ring to read as antique or Art Deco-inspired.

**Milgrain detail** adds a beaded metal border along the outer edge of the halo. It is purely decorative — the milgrain beading references antique hand-engraving techniques and makes a setting look older and more crafted than modern clean-edged designs. The Vintage Inspired Halo by Zac Zac Posen ($3,135) includes milgrain detailing around the halo edge. Milgrain is appropriate for buyers who want a vintage look without the full commitment to heavy hand-engraved detailing.

**Ballerina halo** is a specific architecture where the accent stones are set outward like a tutu — marquise-cut and round accent diamonds alternate around the center stone in a radiating star pattern rather than a flat continuous ring. The Pear Marquise and Round Ballerina Halo ($3,275, platinum) uses this configuration. Ballerina halos have more three-dimensional visual depth than flat pavé halos and create a dramatic starburst appearance when viewed from above. They suit buyers who want maximum visual complexity.

